The paper deals with non-malleable secret sharing and leakage-resilient secret sharing, which are topics related to cryptography and information theory (cs.CR and cs.IT). The paper also discusses tampering models and constructions of secret sharing schemes, which are topics related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper explores the non-compartmentalized model, which is a relatively new area of research in cryptography (cs.CY).
